{
  "texts": [
    "<rdf-model> With ChatGPT-3 only 2/5 iterations succeeded in carrying out all substitutions.",
    "In those succeeding cases, the quality was still not as expected because of limited ontology reuse: Only IRIs in the example namespace were introduced, rather than reusing the foaf, vcard, and org vocabularies.",
    "Yet, the ad-hoc properties and classes were reasonably named, such as eg:firstName, eg:countryName or eg:departmentName.",
    "In contrast, ChatGPT-4 delivered better results: All classes and properties were substituted with those from standard vocabularies-foaf, vcard, and org were correctly identified.",
    "For some iterations, ChatGPT-4 used the schema.org vocabulary instead of the org vocabulary as an alternative approach."
  ]
}